data.title: Confederated Tribes of Grand Ronde
data.text:
The Grand Ronde Tribal Council was created by the Tribal Constitution to be the primary governing and legislative body of the Tribe. The Council consists of nine standing members, each of which is designated to serve three-year terms. Tribal Council members are elected by the Tribal Membership every year during September. There are no restrictions on the number of terms a Council member can serve.

Press & Media

The story of the Confederated Tribes of Grand Ronde is the story of a community, a Tribe, and a culture that has persisted despite the challenges.
